opennlp.ccg.lexicon
Interface Tokenizer

All Known Implementing Classes:
DefaultTokenizer, PipedTokenizer
public interface Tokenizer

The Tokenizer interface provides a way to customize tokenization and handling of special tokens. A custom tokenizer may be specified in the grammar file. DefaultTokenizer provides a default implementation, which can also be subclassed for custom behavior.

Version:
$Revision: 1.14 $, $Date: 2005/10/20 17:30:30 $
Author:

Parses an input string into a list of words, including any explicitly given factors, and the semantic class of special tokens. Tokens are parsed into words using parseToken.
